<TITLE> Soyabean oil price to come down </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 21 (bdnews24.com)  The price of edible soyabean oil will be reduced by Tk 5 per litre from Saturday, said the trade body on Wednesday. "Hopefully the price will go down further," commerce minister Faruk Khan said after a meeting with the president of the edible oil traders association MA Rouf Chowdhury. Chowdhury told the minister in the meeting soyabean oil would go down to Tk 76 from Tk 81. The commerce minister also asked for regular monitoring to ensure that adulterated oil is not marketed and the price is maintained. He also promised the businessmen their problems would be considered. Vice president of the traders association Fazlur Rahman mentioned complaints about pricing related to the weight of bottles. "If the bottle states 900 grammes, then the price of 900 grammes is charged." bdnews24
